::page-section
## Script integration

The first step is to add the following script to **every page** where Bankrate widgets should appear:

```html
<script async src="https://inline.bankrate.com/embed/inlineMedia_core.js"></script>
```

After that script has loaded and you are ready to mount widgets, run the integration initializer:

```html
<script type="text/javascript">
window.initializeInline({
  "overwriteContainer": true,
  "origin": "https://inline.bankrate.com"
});
</script>
```

Together, these scripts are responsible for:

1. **Placement** — Inserting a widget at the location of each placeholder tag on the page.
2. **Resizing** — Handling resize behavior for embedded content.
3. **Tracking** — Attributing widget performance to your page and site.

  ::alert
  ---
  appearance: "warning"
  show-icon: true
  title: "Load order"
  message: "Run initializeInline only after the placeholder tags below are already in the DOM. If placeholders are injected later, widgets will not load. See Troubleshooting for common fixes."
  ---
  ::

::

::page-section
## Placeholder tags

Each widget is a **`<div>`** with class `myFinance-widget`, a unique **`data-ad-id`**, a **`data-campaign`** value, and **`data-s1`** for your sub-ID (replace `PLACESUBIDHERE` with your assigned value).

Under each widget you get:

- **Copy snippet** — Opens the markup as **plain text in a new tab** via a `data:` URL; select all and copy (or use your browser’s copy). If your browser blocks `data:` navigation, copy from the fenced code block above the buttons.
- **Open in MyFinance** — Opens the [TransUnion integration directory](https://www.myfinance.com/integration/transunion-integration-documentation) in a new tab (same hub as the partner UI; use search or filters there to match the widget).

Widgets are grouped by vertical below (**18** total). Refresh from MyFinance if `data-ad-id` / `data-campaign` values change.

